org.mfg.mdb.compiler

Interface IExtensionTargets

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ICompilerExtension

    public interface IExtensionTargets
    The extension targets are the points of an MDB class where the user can inject custom code via a compiler extension.
    Author:
    arian
    See Also:
    ICompilerExtension

    • Field Detail

      • TARGET_MDB_CLASS

        static final java.lang.String TARGET_MDB_CLASS
        Refers to the body of an MDB class. You can use this to add custom MDB classes members like fields, methods, etc...

      • TARGET_MDB_CLASS_APPEND_METHOD

        static final java.lang.String TARGET_MDB_CLASS_APPEND_METHOD
        Refers to the end of the append() methods of an MDB class. Use this target to add custom statements at the end of the method. See the example of the ICompilerExtension javadoc.
